This paper is about multi-robot path planning, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves using a combination of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and graph neural networks (GNNs) to learn a decentralized sequential action policy, which is a type of machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the training and evaluation of the model, which involves measuring success rates and costs, indicating a focus on optimization and learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of local communication and decision-making, which is a characteristic of distributed systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the generalization of the model to previously unseen cases, which is a topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA).
